Since $\triangle AOB$ and $\triangle BOC$ are isosceles with $AO = BO = CO = 10,$ $\angle ABO = \angle BCO = \frac{\pi - \theta}{2}$ and $\angle BOA = \angle COB = \frac{\pi - \phi}{2}.$

Then $\angle DOA = \angle COB = \pi - \theta - \phi,$ so $\angle AOP = \frac{\pi - (\pi - \theta - \phi)}{2} = \frac{\theta + \phi}{2}.$  Similarly, $\angle POB = \frac{\pi - (\pi - \theta - \phi)}{2} = \frac{\theta + \phi}{2}.$

