Let $h$ be the height of the trapezoid $ABCD,$ and let $h_1$ and $h_2$ be the heights of trapezoids $ABYX$ and $XYCD,$ respectively.  Then
\begin{align*}
h &= 10 + 10 + 12 \cos \theta + 12 \cos \phi \\
h_1 &= 10 + 10 + 12 \cos \theta + 10 \cos \frac{\theta + \phi}{2} \\
h_2 &= 10 + 10 + 12 \cos \phi + 10 \cos \frac{\theta + \phi}{2}.
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines on triangle $AOB,$
\[\cos \theta = \frac{10^2 + 10^2 - 12^2}{2 \cdot 10 \cdot 10} = -\frac{1}{5}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $BOC,$
\[\cos \phi = \frac{10^2 + 10^2 - 12^2}{2 \cdot 10 \cdot 10} = -\frac{1}{5}.\]Then
\[\cos \frac{\theta + \phi}{2} = \sqrt{\frac{1 + \cos (\theta + \phi)}{2}} = \sqrt{\frac{1 - \cos (\pi - \theta - \phi)}{2}} = \sqrt{\frac{1 + \cos (\theta + \phi)}{2}}.\]Since $\cos (\theta + \phi) = \cos \theta \cos \phi - \sin \theta \sin \phi = \frac{1}{25} - \sin \theta \sin \phi,$
\[\cos \frac{\theta + \phi}{2} = \sqrt{\frac{13}{25} - \frac{1}{25} \sin \theta \sin \phi}.\]Therefore,
\begin{align*}
h &= 10 + 10 + 12 \cdot \left( -\frac{1}{5} \right) + 12 \cdot \left( -\frac{1}{5} \right) = 16, \\
h_1 &= 10 + 10 + 12 \cdot \left( -\frac{1}{5} \right) + 10 \sqrt{\frac{13}{25} - \frac{1}{25} \sin \theta \sin \phi}, \\
h_2 &= 10 + 10 + 12 \cdot \left( -\frac{1}{5} \right) + 10 \sqrt{\frac{13}{25} - \frac{1}{25} \sin \theta \sin \phi}.
\end{align*}Therefore,
\[\frac{h_1}{h_2} = \frac{10 + 10 + 12 \cdot \left( -\frac{1}{5} \right) + 10 \sqrt{\frac{13}{25} - \frac{1}{25} \sin \theta \sin \phi}}{10 + 10 + 12 \cdot \left( -\frac{1}{5} \right) + 10 \sqrt{\frac{13}{25} - \frac{1}{25} \sin \theta \sin \phi}} = 1,\]so $p + q = \boxed{1}.$
